In .NET MAUI, use `Application.Current.RequestedTheme` and the `RequestedThemeChanged` event:

**Detect & subscribe to system theme changes:**

```csharp
// Read current theme
AppTheme current = Application.Current!.RequestedTheme; // Dark or Light

// React in real time
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to {e.RequestedTheme}");
    // Update UI or re-apply resources here
};
```

**Force a specific theme (override system setting):**

```csharp
// Lock to dark mode regardless of device setting
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Revert to following the system
Application.Current!.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

**Auto-switch resources in XAML** using `AppThemeBinding`:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Black, Dark=White}"
       BackgroundColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=White, Dark=#1E1E1E}" />
```

**Key points:**
- `RequestedTheme` — read-only, reflects the OS setting.
- `UserAppTheme` — read/write, your app-level override. Set to `AppTheme.Unspecified` to follow the system again.
- `AppThemeBinding` in XAML reacts automatically to both system and user-forced changes — no code-behind needed for simple color swaps.
